@startuml wake-sequence
' Waking a hibernated Agent: lazy connect-fail detection, the activator call, and the watch-driven reconcile.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/user/activation-and-activity.md
!include _style.puml

actor "Webhook\ncaller" as caller
participant "User\nGateway" as gw #90EE90
participant "Agent\nService" as agent
participant "Controller\nactivator :9443\n**ANY replica**" as ctrl #87CEEB
participant "apiserver" as api #FFD580
participant "Controller **LEADER**\nAgentReconciler" as leader #87CEEB

caller -> gw : channel message for a\nHibernated Agent
gw ->x agent : dial POST /v1/message
note over gw, agent
  **Connect failure is the whole detection mechanism.**
  TCP RST (iptables kube-proxy), or a connect timeout
  within agentDeliveryConnectTimeout (1s) on paths that
  drop to empty-endpoint ClusterIPs (IPVS, Cilium, eBPF).
  There is no Endpoint or EndpointSlice watch.
end note

alt #FFF8DC controller reachable
  gw -> ctrl : POST /v1/activate/{ns}/{name} (mTLS)
  ctrl -> api : patch agentry.io/wake=true
  ctrl --> gw : **202 Accepted**

  note over gw, ctrl #FFE4B5
    **The 202 precedes the wake.**
    It confirms the annotation was written,
    not that the Agent is coming up.
  end note

  api -> leader : Agent watch fires (**leader only**)
  leader -> leader : step 9:\nHibernated\n-> Resuming
  leader -> api : recreate Pod

  note over ctrl, leader #FFE4B5
    **The replica that took the call is not**
    **the one that does the work.**
    The apiserver is the message bus, which is
    why the handler need not run on the leader.
  end note

  loop until Ready, bounded by wakeTimeout (120s)
    gw -> agent : poll readiness
  end
  note over gw, agent
    The gateway **polls the Agent Service** for readiness.
    It does not learn it from the activator response.
  end note

  alt Pod Ready within wakeTimeout
    gw -> agent : POST /v1/message (deliver)
    agent --> gw : response envelope
    gw --> caller : reply (sync inline, or async\nvia callbackUrl / polling)
  else wakeTimeout (120s) exceeded
    gw --> caller : **wake_timeout**\nsync: 504 | async: error payload to\ncallbackUrl or the polling endpoint
  end

else controller unreachable
  note over gw, ctrl
    Connection refused, TLS handshake failure, client-cert
    SAN rejection, or 5xx after one internal retry.
  end note
  gw --> caller : **controller_unavailable**\nsync: 504 + **Retry-After: 5**\nasync: error payload
  note over gw, ctrl
    The wake was never attempted and the Agent stays
    **Hibernated**. Retry is expected to succeed once
    the controller recovers, hence retryable: true.
  end note
end
@enduml
